meme

Trump is laughing. 

library(magick)
#link
Trump_laugh <- image_read("https://media.vanityfair.com/photos/5debe3107dad0f000808b8cc/master/pass/donald-trump.jpg") %>%
  image_resize("450x450!")

#blank size and color
new_blank <- image_blank(width = 450, height = 450, 
                         color = "#FF0000") %>%
  
#text
  image_annotate(text = "HAHAHAHAHA LOL!", color = "#FFFFFF", size = 60, 
                 font = "Impact", gravity = "center")

#The new
new_meme <- image_append(c(new_blank, Trump_laugh))

#Save new
image_write(new_meme, "my_meme.png")

new_meme

GIF

This is a GIF about cat. 

library(magick)

# the frame 
cat1 <- image_read("https://cdn.britannica.com/19/213119-050-C81C786D/Grumpy-Cat-2015-memes.jpg")%>%
  image_resize("310x310")

cat2 <- image_read("https://media.wired.com/photos/60b039490744ea4218d0e6de/master/pass/Gear-Make-Your-Own-Memes-459583554.jpg")%>%
  image_resize("310x310")

cat3 <- image_read("https://c0.lestechnophiles.com/www.numerama.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/grumpycat-680x383.jpg?resize=310,330&key=b14a24b1")%>%
  image_resize("310x310")

cat4 <- image_read("https://res.cloudinary.com/wired-de/image/upload/t_intro/meme-36372.jpg.jpg")%>%
  image_resize("310x310")

# combine the frame
animation <- c(cat1, cat2, cat3, cat4)

# creating an animation
image_animate(animation, fps = 2)

# the fig
image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
